        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Calculated value. 

Global surfactant demand is estimated to be 15.93 million tons in 2014 from article from Grand View Research, Inc., author Sherry James, November 18 2015, title: Surfactants Market to Be Worth $46.20 Billion by 2022: Grand View Research, Inc., Retrieved from: http://www.marketwired.com/press-release/surfactants-market-to-be-worth-4620-billion-by-2022-grand-view-research-inc-2074859.htm.

In 2002 the non-ionic surfactants represented 40% of global demand of surfactants. Of the non-ionic surfactants, the main groups are: 40% Ethoxylated Linear Alcohols, 20% Fatty Acid Esters, 15% Ethoxylated Alkyl Phenols, 10% Amine and Amide Derivatives. These products are used as cleaning and wetting agents, for emulsification and foaming. Certain surfactants are not harmful and can therefore be used in the pharmaceutical, cosmetics and food industry (Salager 2002). This dataset represents the production of non-ionic surfactants using ethylene oxide.

Reference(s):
Salager, J. 2002. Surfactants Types and Uses. UNIVERSIDAD DE LOS ANDES FACULTAD DE INGENIERIA ESCUELA DE INGENIERIA QUIMICA. Retrieved from: http://www.nanoparticles.org/pdf/Salager-E300A.pdf, accessed 27 January 2017
</productionVolumeComment>
