      <intermediateExchange id="cd6ba478-53c7-5580-870c-6bb5c0e38ec6" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" casNumber="111-42-2" amount="0.426657702016892" intermediateExchangeId="12b2f717-a83f-4848-91c5-9f081b030ae5" activityLinkId="9460d9f9-f5c4-58a6-b8ec-70f15330b921">
        <name xml:lang="en">diethanolamine</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Calculated value based on stoichiometric calculations and literature data. 
105.13688g/mol is the molar mass of diethanolamine (C4H11NO2). 
 

The product is the result of the reaction of fatty acids from coconut oil and diethanolamine.
Chemical reaction:
CH3(CH2)nCOOH + C4H11NO2 -&gt; CH3(CH2)nC(=O)N(CH2CH2OH)2
Where n = 8-18
Here n is assumed to be n=8
CH3(CH2)8COOH + C4H11NO2 -&gt; CH3(CH2)8C(=O)N(CH2CH2OH)2</comment>
        <uncertainty>
          <lognormal meanValue="0.426657702016892" mu="-0.8517732218552252" variance="0.0006" varianceWithPedigreeUncertainty="0.010025"/>
          <pedigreeMatrix reliability="2" completeness="3" temporalCorrelation="2" geographicalCorrelation="2" furtherTechnologyCorrelation="3"/>
        </uncertainty>
