      <intermediateExchange id="201153ff-d974-5728-87fb-470e0889ed46" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" amount="0.699081981013372" intermediateExchangeId="4aeb3a6c-81f4-4f6e-80b6-797b812e0792" activityLinkId="d1eb18e7-dcaf-5ca6-868c-f21b86552c89">
        <name xml:lang="en">fatty acid</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Calculated value based on stoichiometric calculations and literature data. 
74.07944g/mol is the molar mass of fatty acid (C3H6O2). 
 

The product is the result of the reaction of fatty acids from coconut oil and diethanolamine.
Chemical reaction:
CH3(CH2)nCOOH + C4H11NO2 -&gt; CH3(CH2)nC(=O)N(CH2CH2OH)2
Where n = 8-18
Here n is assumed to be n=8
CH3(CH2)8COOH + C4H11NO2 -&gt; CH3(CH2)8C(=O)N(CH2CH2OH)2

This was taken as an example reaction to calculate stoichiometry, the input to the activity is though a generic fatty acid as other fatty acids can be used to produce non-ionic surfactant.</comment>
